Text.SourceString: This vile slime...it seeps into everything, darkening our kingdom.
Text.LocalizedString: This vile slime...it seeps into everything, darkening our kingdom.

Text.SourceString: Ah, splendid. More of that accursed slime. Hmmph.
Text.LocalizedString: Ah, splendid. More of that accursed slime. Hmmph.

Text.SourceString: I've never come across anything quite so...disheartening.//<portrait=annoyed>Not in my previous kingdom, and certainly not here until this slime appeared.
Text.LocalizedString: I've never come across anything quite so...disheartening.//<portrait=annoyed>Not in my previous kingdom, and certainly not here until this slime appeared.

Text.SourceString: History has taught us that we can't afford optimism in the face of such adversity.//This dark slime is a true test of our almight Kingdom.
Text.LocalizedString: History has taught us that we can't afford optimism in the face of such adversity.//This dark slime is a true test of our almight Kingdom.

Text.SourceString: The situation we find ourselves in...//<portrait=concerned>Thruth be told, I have seen more hopeful prospects in a shipwreck...yes.//<portrait=annoyed>When the depths of the sea offer more hope than our current state, it's clear we're in dire straits.
Text.LocalizedString: The situation we find ourselves in...//<portrait=concerned>Thruth be told, I have seen more hopeful prospects in a shipwreck...yes.//<portrait=annoyed>When the depths of the sea offer more hope than our current state, it's clear we're in dire straits.

Text.SourceString: The timing of your arrival is uncanny, land-dweller.//I shall keep my sceptre at hand and my expectations firmly in check.
Text.LocalizedString: The timing of your arrival is uncanny, land-dweller.//I shall keep my sceptre at hand and my expectations firmly in check.

Text.SourceString: Our consensus to allow your presence in our realm is...less than ideal.//It is unnatural.
Text.LocalizedString: Our consensus to allow your presence in our realm is...less than ideal.//It is unnatural.

Text.SourceString: I suppose we must bear with your presence...at least for the time being.
Text.LocalizedString: I suppose we must bear with your presence...at least for the time being.

Text.SourceString: As the Queen, I'm accustomed to the unexpected, yet your presence in our court is...jarring...yes.//What precisely <NPCName>Cho Oyu</> and <NPCName>Miranjani</> see in you, I confess, is beyond my comprehension.
Text.LocalizedString: As the Queen, I'm accustomed to the unexpected, yet your presence in our court is...jarring...yes.//What precisely <NPCName>Cho Oyu</> and <NPCName>Miranjani</> see in you, I confess, is beyond my comprehension.

Text.SourceString: Allow me to extend our hospitality, land-dweller.//<portrait=normal>I implore you not to grow overly complacent in our midst.
Text.LocalizedString: Allow me to extend our hospitality, land-dweller.//<portrait=normal>I implore you not to grow overly complacent in our midst.

Text.SourceString: I must say...your engagement in this quest for <Italic>my</> kingdom piques my curiosity.
Text.LocalizedString: I must say...your engagement in this quest for <Italic>my</> kingdom piques my curiosity.

Text.SourceString: Yes, yes, we've all heard about the wonderful agreement you've made with the Kingdom. Let's move on.
Text.LocalizedString: Yes, yes, we've all heard about the wonderful agreement you've made with the Kingdom. Let's move on.

Text.SourceString: I have indeed encountered your kind before...ah, yes.//The typical land-dwellers, arriving here with their grand schemes.//<portrait=normal>Some, and pardon my forthrightness, regrettably, have ushered in burdens instead.
Text.LocalizedString: I have indeed encountered your kind before...ah, yes.//The typical land-dwellers, arriving here with their grand schemes.//<portrait=normal>Some, and pardon my forthrightness, regrettably, have ushered in burdens instead.

Text.SourceString: It's surprising to see you adapt so quickly. How...impressive.//Your rapid adaptation to <Italic>my</> world, with your land-bound heritage not slowing you down. Hmmph.
Text.LocalizedString: It's surprising to see you adapt so quickly. How...impressive.//Your rapid adaptation to <Italic>my</> world, with your land-bound heritage not slowing you down. Hmmph.

Text.SourceString: To think the almighty <NPCName>Goddess</> would send us a farmer, from the surface world no less, to mend our wounds, how...quaint.
Text.LocalizedString: To think the almighty <NPCName>Goddess</> would send us a farmer, from the surface world no less, to mend our wounds, how...quaint.

Text.SourceString: Your naïveté shines brighter than a pearl, land-dweller.//<portrait=happy>But perhaps that's not entirely unfavorable.
Text.LocalizedString: Your naïveté shines brighter than a pearl, land-dweller.//<portrait=happy>But perhaps that's not entirely unfavorable.

Text.SourceString: Occasionally, someone...unassuming could be exactly what is necessary.
Text.LocalizedString: Occasionally, someone...unassuming could be exactly what is necessary.

Text.SourceString: I have a lot of respect for farmers, so tell me, what type of crops do you cultivate to serve your community?
Text.LocalizedString: I have a lot of respect for farmers, so tell me, what type of crops do you cultivate to serve your community?

Text.SourceString: I see you've managed to navigate our waterways without getting lost. Bravo.
Text.LocalizedString: I see you've managed to navigate our waterways without getting lost. Bravo.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Cho Oyu</> informed us that she witnessed your assistance, a notion that was initially challenging to embrace. Hmmph.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Cho Oyu</> informed us that she witnessed your assistance, a notion that was initially challenging to embrace. Hmmph.

Text.SourceString: However, we are grateful for your aid, land-dweller...yes.//<portrait=happy>After all, one can never have too many...simple hands on deck.
Text.LocalizedString: However, we are grateful for your aid, land-dweller...yes.//<portrait=happy>After all, one can never have too many...simple hands on deck.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Princess Miranjani</> seems...fascinated by your kind. I understand her curiosity.//<portrait=normal>After all, she is still young and unversed in the complexities of the real world.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Princess Miranjani</> seems...fascinated by your kind. I understand her curiosity.//<portrait=normal>After all, she is still young and unversed in the complexities of the real world.

Text.SourceString: His Majesty and I have a stable full of seahorses. As an individual of agrarian pursuits, this might intrigue you.//I suggest you explore it.
Text.LocalizedString: His Majesty and I have a stable full of seahorses. As an individual of agrarian pursuits, this might intrigue you.//I suggest you explore it.

Text.SourceString: Why not have <NpcName>Semeru</> as your guide? He would be more than willing to provide a tour.//<portrait=happy>Shall I call upon the Lead Guard?
Text.LocalizedString: Why not have <NpcName>Semeru</> as your guide? He would be more than willing to provide a tour.//<portrait=happy>Shall I call upon the Lead Guard?

Text.SourceString: Oh, you managed to clear that all on your own? How...fascinating.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, you managed to clear that all on your own? How...fascinating.

Text.SourceString: It seems your work has started to make an impact.//I must admit the water is clearer...yes.
Text.LocalizedString: It seems your work has started to make an impact.//I must admit the water is clearer...yes.

Text.SourceString: Well, well, look at the progress. An area cleared...we find ourselves in your debt.//<portrait=happy>Truly, you surprise me.
Text.LocalizedString: Well, well, look at the progress. An area cleared...we find ourselves in your debt.//<portrait=happy>Truly, you surprise me.

Text.SourceString: The current seems gentler, more harmonious lately.
Text.LocalizedString: The current seems gentler, more harmonious lately.

Text.SourceString: The murmur among the fish is more cheerful...they appear content.
Text.LocalizedString: The murmur among the fish is more cheerful...they appear content.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Princess Miranjani</> shows a keen desire to explore...again. Yes, hmmph.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Princess Miranjani</> shows a keen desire to explore...again. Yes, hmmph.

Text.SourceString: I can understand the allure, particularly with the water's captivating clarity.//However, without guards, it would be a definitive no.
Text.LocalizedString: I can understand the allure, particularly with the water's captivating clarity.//However, without guards, it would be a definitive no.

Text.SourceString: I must confess that chatting is not in the cards for me at this moment. My apologies.
Text.LocalizedString: I must confess that chatting is not in the cards for me at this moment. My apologies.

Text.SourceString: I must take my leave now, but please feel free to immerse yourself further.
Text.LocalizedString: I must take my leave now, but please feel free to immerse yourself further.

Text.SourceString: Please excuse me.
Text.LocalizedString: Please excuse me.

Text.SourceString: The dish <NpcName>Olan</> has crafted has notably improved...owing, he claims, to fresher, superior produce.
Text.LocalizedString: The dish <NpcName>Olan</> has crafted has notably improved...owing, he claims, to fresher, superior produce.

Text.SourceString: The currents seem to have found a new rhythm, a harmony born from the cleared space.//A welcome change, indeed.
Text.LocalizedString: The currents seem to have found a new rhythm, a harmony born from the cleared space.//A welcome change, indeed.

Text.SourceString: The Kingdom has been experiencing a shift towards positivity lately. Ah, yes...
Text.LocalizedString: The Kingdom has been experiencing a shift towards positivity lately. Ah, yes...

Text.SourceString: I've been informed that much of it is attributed to your efforts.//<portrait=normal>Please accept my heartfelt gratitude, <PlayerName>$Player</>.
Text.LocalizedString: I've been informed that much of it is attributed to your efforts.//<portrait=normal>Please accept my heartfelt gratitude, <PlayerName>$Player</>.

Text.SourceString: As the Queen of this Kingdom, I bestow upon you a blessing of grace upon your tail.//May it guide you on your underwater adventures, filled with wonder and amazement.
Text.LocalizedString: As the Queen of this Kingdom, I bestow upon you a blessing of grace upon your tail.//May it guide you on your underwater adventures, filled with wonder and amazement.

Text.SourceString: Tails fit you. You're one of us now, <PlayerName>$Player</>.
Text.LocalizedString: Tails fit you. You're one of us now, <PlayerName>$Player</>.

Text.SourceString: Your naïveté shines brighter than a pearl, land-dweller.//<portrait=happy>But perhaps that's not entirely unfavorable.
Text.LocalizedString: Your naïveté shines brighter than a pearl, land-dweller.//<portrait=happy>But perhaps that's not entirely unfavorable.

Text.SourceString: Occasionally, someone...unassuming could be exactly what is necessary.
Text.LocalizedString: Occasionally, someone...unassuming could be exactly what is necessary.

Text.SourceString: I have a lot of respect for farmers, so tell me, what type of crops do you cultivate to serve your community?
Text.LocalizedString: I have a lot of respect for farmers, so tell me, what type of crops do you cultivate to serve your community?

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Princess Miranjani</> shows a keen desire to explore...again. Yes, hmmph.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Princess Miranjani</> shows a keen desire to explore...again. Yes, hmmph.

Text.SourceString: I can understand the allure, particularly with the water's captivating clarity.//However, without guards, it would be a definitive no.
Text.LocalizedString: I can understand the allure, particularly with the water's captivating clarity.//However, without guards, it would be a definitive no.

Text.SourceString: I must confess that chatting is not in the cards for me at this moment. My apologies.
Text.LocalizedString: I must confess that chatting is not in the cards for me at this moment. My apologies.

Text.SourceString: I must take my leave now, but please feel free to immerse yourself further.
Text.LocalizedString: I must take my leave now, but please feel free to immerse yourself further.

Text.SourceString: Please excuse me.
Text.LocalizedString: Please excuse me.

Text.SourceString: Back in my school days in the North Pole, we played a daring game where some of us would race to the surface, but getting caught by the guards resulted in a punishment in the deep dungeons.//<portrait=normal>The King was always the reigning champion.
Text.LocalizedString: Back in my school days in the North Pole, we played a daring game where some of us would race to the surface, but getting caught by the guards resulted in a punishment in the deep dungeons.//<portrait=normal>The King was always the reigning champion.

Text.SourceString: Initially, the thought of being sent to the dungeons was frightening, but I soon realized it was all in good fun and perfectly safe.//it help no real fear in me.
Text.LocalizedString: Initially, the thought of being sent to the dungeons was frightening, but I soon realized it was all in good fun and perfectly safe.//it help no real fear in me.

Text.SourceString: I spent countless hours practicing the art of underwater calligraphy, a skill highly prized in Atlantoria.
Text.LocalizedString: I spent countless hours practicing the art of underwater calligraphy, a skill highly prized in Atlantoria.

Text.SourceString: I also immersed myself in the study of our ancient texts, learning the history and lore of our people.
Text.LocalizedString: I also immersed myself in the study of our ancient texts, learning the history and lore of our people.

Text.SourceString: I still remember my first encounter with the King. He was so kind.
Text.LocalizedString: I still remember my first encounter with the King. He was so kind.

Text.SourceString: As a child, my time in Atlantoria was an essential part of my royal upbringing.//It was a tradition, one that my parents, and their parents before them, all followed.
Text.LocalizedString: As a child, my time in Atlantoria was an essential part of my royal upbringing.//It was a tradition, one that my parents, and their parents before them, all followed.

Text.SourceString: The cold waters in the North Pole were initially a shock, far chillier than in my own kingdom, but one adapts over time.
Text.LocalizedString: The cold waters in the North Pole were initially a shock, far chillier than in my own kingdom, but one adapts over time.

Text.SourceString: The darkness of Atlantoria's depths had a certain calmness, a stark contrast to the brighter waters of my kingdom.
Text.LocalizedString: The darkness of Atlantoria's depths had a certain calmness, a stark contrast to the brighter waters of my kingdom.

Text.SourceString: As a child, I used to spend hours watching the curious dances of the seahorses in the royal gardens, it was fascinating.
Text.LocalizedString: As a child, I used to spend hours watching the curious dances of the seahorses in the royal gardens, it was fascinating.

Text.SourceString: One of my cherished memories is collecting glowing algae at night, creating a shimmering spectacle in the dark waters
Text.LocalizedString: One of my cherished memories is collecting glowing algae at night, creating a shimmering spectacle in the dark waters

Text.SourceString: I remember the thrill of my first solo swim to the Great Kelp Maze, a rite of passage for every young merchild in our kingdom.//<portrait=happy>Mira did exceptionally well on hers; the King and I were very proud.
Text.LocalizedString: I remember the thrill of my first solo swim to the Great Kelp Maze, a rite of passage for every young merchild in our kingdom.//<portrait=happy>Mira did exceptionally well on hers; the King and I were very proud.

Text.SourceString: Learning underwater gardening from my grandmother is a memory I treasure deeply. Together, we tended to exotic aquatic plants.//<portrait=happy>She was truly an exceptional gardener.
Text.LocalizedString: Learning underwater gardening from my grandmother is a memory I treasure deeply. Together, we tended to exotic aquatic plants.//<portrait=happy>She was truly an exceptional gardener.

Text.SourceString: Underwater gardening brings me peace; nurturing sea flora has always been a passion of mine.//<portrait=happy>So, tell me, what tips can you share, as a fellow farmer?
Text.LocalizedString: Underwater gardening brings me peace; nurturing sea flora has always been a passion of mine.//<portrait=happy>So, tell me, what tips can you share, as a fellow farmer?

Text.SourceString: I've always been fascinated by the arts and history, both of our people and yours, <PlayerName>$Player</>. I once received a gift – twin statues crafted by ancient land dwellers.//<portrait=normal>We've placed them at the gate; this was long before your time, many moons ago.
Text.LocalizedString: I've always been fascinated by the arts and history, both of our people and yours, <PlayerName>$Player</>. I once received a gift – twin statues crafted by ancient land dwellers.//<portrait=normal>We've placed them at the gate; this was long before your time, many moons ago.

Text.SourceString: Creating underwater mosaics with shells and stones is a beloved hobby of mine, a way to unwind and channel my creativity.
Text.LocalizedString: Creating underwater mosaics with shells and stones is a beloved hobby of mine, a way to unwind and channel my creativity.

Text.SourceString: In my younger years, I oversaw the kingdom's relics, and the Wall of Relic that I curated still stands proudly.
Text.LocalizedString: In my younger years, I oversaw the kingdom's relics, and the Wall of Relic that I curated still stands proudly.

Text.SourceString: Balancing the roles of a mother and a queen, I aim to be a role model for Mira, though I admit some days are more challenging than others.
Text.LocalizedString: Balancing the roles of a mother and a queen, I aim to be a role model for Mira, though I admit some days are more challenging than others.

Text.SourceString: Educating Mira about our kingdom is a lesson in patience and understanding for me too, particularly in patience.//<portrait=annoyed>I must confess, dealing with human trinkets can be rather trying at times.
Text.LocalizedString: Educating Mira about our kingdom is a lesson in patience and understanding for me too, particularly in patience.//<portrait=annoyed>I must confess, dealing with human trinkets can be rather trying at times.

Text.SourceString: Providing Mira with both love and wisdom is as essential as any of my duties as a queen. While I am relieved that the King rules the kingdom, I am fully prepared to step in if needed.//<portrait=concerned>Let's just hope it never comes to that.
Text.LocalizedString: Providing Mira with both love and wisdom is as essential as any of my duties as a queen. While I am relieved that the King rules the kingdom, I am fully prepared to step in if needed.//<portrait=concerned>Let's just hope it never comes to that.

Text.SourceString: We have made strides in gender equality, creating opportunities for mermaids in all fields of our kingdom.
Text.LocalizedString: We have made strides in gender equality, creating opportunities for mermaids in all fields of our kingdom.

Text.SourceString: In the ocean's deepest abyss, where darkness prevails, I once encountered giant squids.//<portrait=happy>It was a fascinating experience; those squids are surprisingly sensitive creatures.
Text.LocalizedString: In the ocean's deepest abyss, where darkness prevails, I once encountered giant squids.//<portrait=happy>It was a fascinating experience; those squids are surprisingly sensitive creatures.

Text.SourceString: Mira's closeness to her aunt Liang was heartwarming; she took her departure to the land above quite hard.
Text.LocalizedString: Mira's closeness to her aunt Liang was heartwarming; she took her departure to the land above quite hard.

Text.SourceString: Mira always wanted to fit in, but her secret trips to mingle with Atlantoria's commonfolk gave us quite a few scares.
Text.LocalizedString: Mira always wanted to fit in, but her secret trips to mingle with Atlantoria's commonfolk gave us quite a few scares.

Text.SourceString: Our family faced moments of tension when Mira's grandparents learned of her sneaking out, worried about the risks involved.//She needs to start behaving like the royal she is, after all.
Text.LocalizedString: Our family faced moments of tension when Mira's grandparents learned of her sneaking out, worried about the risks involved.//She needs to start behaving like the royal she is, after all.

Text.SourceString: Sending royal children to the North Pole school is a longstanding custom, essential for their growth into capable leaders.
Text.LocalizedString: Sending royal children to the North Pole school is a longstanding custom, essential for their growth into capable leaders.

Text.SourceString: At the North Pole school, it's not just book learning; it's about shaping values and skills for life.
Text.LocalizedString: At the North Pole school, it's not just book learning; it's about shaping values and skills for life.

Text.SourceString: There are quiet evenings where the King and I simply enjoy the tranquility of our gardens, a rare respite from our royal duties.//Perhaps my favorite way to pass the time.
Text.LocalizedString: There are quiet evenings where the King and I simply enjoy the tranquility of our gardens, a rare respite from our royal duties.//Perhaps my favorite way to pass the time.

Text.SourceString: I cherish the moments when we escape our royal personas, like our secret swims to the hidden coral reefs, just to enjoy each other's company.
Text.LocalizedString: I cherish the moments when we escape our royal personas, like our secret swims to the hidden coral reefs, just to enjoy each other's company.

Text.SourceString: Celebrating our anniversaries is always special; each year, the King surprises me with a new sea flower bed in Atlantoria.//<portrait=normal>It's become a cherished tradition of ours.
Text.LocalizedString: Celebrating our anniversaries is always special; each year, the King surprises me with a new sea flower bed in Atlantoria.//<portrait=normal>It's become a cherished tradition of ours.

Text.SourceString: Part of my duties involves resolving disputes among sea creatures, such as the territorial debates between the crab clans and the anemone societies.//<portrait=concerned>That particular one was tough; nobody was willing to compromise.
Text.LocalizedString: Part of my duties involves resolving disputes among sea creatures, such as the territorial debates between the crab clans and the anemone societies.//<portrait=concerned>That particular one was tough; nobody was willing to compromise.

Text.SourceString: Our palace gardens serve as a model for sustainable underwater farming, showing how we can harvest food without harming the ecosystem.
Text.LocalizedString: Our palace gardens serve as a model for sustainable underwater farming, showing how we can harvest food without harming the ecosystem.

Text.SourceString: Apart from her role as an oracle, Cho Oyu has been a nurturing presence in Mira's life, watching over her since she was a mere hatchling.
Text.LocalizedString: Apart from her role as an oracle, Cho Oyu has been a nurturing presence in Mira's life, watching over her since she was a mere hatchling.

Text.SourceString: Cho Oyu's foresight has been invaluable, not just in matters of state but in personal affairs too, guiding us through complex royal decisions.
Text.LocalizedString: Cho Oyu's foresight has been invaluable, not just in matters of state but in personal affairs too, guiding us through complex royal decisions.

Text.SourceString: Cho Oyu has declined to live within the kingdom, fearing it may hinder the clarity of her visions.//<portrait=annoyed>What do you think about that? Should I take offense?
Text.LocalizedString: Cho Oyu has declined to live within the kingdom, fearing it may hinder the clarity of her visions.//<portrait=annoyed>What do you think about that? Should I take offense?

Text.SourceString: Cho Oyu is unable to live away from the coral tree; her survival is intricately linked to its presence.
Text.LocalizedString: Cho Oyu is unable to live away from the coral tree; her survival is intricately linked to its presence.

Text.SourceString: In essence, Cho Oyu is bound to reside here, near the coral tree, as her life force is deeply connected to it, making living elsewhere impossible for her.
Text.LocalizedString: In essence, Cho Oyu is bound to reside here, near the coral tree, as her life force is deeply connected to it, making living elsewhere impossible for her.

Text.SourceString: Miranjani once suggested gifting one of her tiaras to her pet, not realizing the magnitude of giving away a queen's tiara.
Text.LocalizedString: Miranjani once suggested gifting one of her tiaras to her pet, not realizing the magnitude of giving away a queen's tiara.

Text.SourceString: While I appreciate Mira's playful nature, a queen's tiara is a symbol of royalty and history, not quite suitable for a pet's adornment.
Text.LocalizedString: While I appreciate Mira's playful nature, a queen's tiara is a symbol of royalty and history, not quite suitable for a pet's adornment.

Text.SourceString: I have to admit, when Mira dressed up Putput in one of my tiaras, the sight was quite endearing.//<portrait=normal>That girl certainly has a taste for expensive hobbies.
Text.LocalizedString: I have to admit, when Mira dressed up Putput in one of my tiaras, the sight was quite endearing.//<portrait=normal>That girl certainly has a taste for expensive hobbies.

Text.SourceString: I have tiaras for every occasion; some are heirlooms from generations past, while others are gifts from foreign dignitaries, each with unique significance.
Text.LocalizedString: I have tiaras for every occasion; some are heirlooms from generations past, while others are gifts from foreign dignitaries, each with unique significance.

Text.SourceString: In our tradition, when a royal reaches a certain age, they receive a custom tiara set. I've worn mine for so many moons, it feels like a part of me now.//<portrait=happy>Interestingly, it was crafted by the same jeweler who made Miranjani's.
Text.LocalizedString: In our tradition, when a royal reaches a certain age, they receive a custom tiara set. I've worn mine for so many moons, it feels like a part of me now.//<portrait=happy>Interestingly, it was crafted by the same jeweler who made Miranjani's.

Text.SourceString: The necklace of pearls I wear is a treasured heirloom from the King's great-grandmother.//<portrait=normal>It's a piece of Atlantoria's heritage, and one day, it will be passed down to Miranjani.
Text.LocalizedString: The necklace of pearls I wear is a treasured heirloom from the King's great-grandmother.//<portrait=normal>It's a piece of Atlantoria's heritage, and one day, it will be passed down to Miranjani.

Text.SourceString: I've always found it fascinating how land dwellers adorn themselves with so many layers of fabric, a stark contrast to our simple sea attire.
Text.LocalizedString: I've always found it fascinating how land dwellers adorn themselves with so many layers of fabric, a stark contrast to our simple sea attire.

Text.SourceString: Land dwellers' use of fabric is not just for warmth, I've noticed, but also a canvas for expressing their personalities and traditions.
Text.LocalizedString: Land dwellers' use of fabric is not just for warmth, I've noticed, but also a canvas for expressing their personalities and traditions.

Text.SourceString: Their seasonal fashion changes, adapting to the environment, is a concept quite alien, as we merfolk have little need for such adjustments.
Text.LocalizedString: Their seasonal fashion changes, adapting to the environment, is a concept quite alien, as we merfolk have little need for such adjustments.

Text.SourceString: As much as I appreciate the wonders of the land, there's a deep sense of belonging I feel here in the ocean's depths, right where I was meant to be.
Text.LocalizedString: As much as I appreciate the wonders of the land, there's a deep sense of belonging I feel here in the ocean's depths, right where I was meant to be.

Text.SourceString: Many of the plants in our garden are not native; I've brought them from my own kingdom as a small reminder of home.
Text.LocalizedString: Many of the plants in our garden are not native; I've brought them from my own kingdom as a small reminder of home.

Text.SourceString: Seeing our villagers take up gardening is heartwarming.//I've always believed in growing our own food rather than harvesting it from wild nature.
Text.LocalizedString: Seeing our villagers take up gardening is heartwarming.//I've always believed in growing our own food rather than harvesting it from wild nature.

Text.SourceString: The gardens that supply our kingdom with food are situated a few days' journey from here, in waters that are better suited for cultivating a diverse range of crops.
Text.LocalizedString: The gardens that supply our kingdom with food are situated a few days' journey from here, in waters that are better suited for cultivating a diverse range of crops.

Text.SourceString: Olan has been with our family for ages. Yet, his love for travel makes me wonder if we'll one day be searching for a new head chef.
Text.LocalizedString: Olan has been with our family for ages. Yet, his love for travel makes me wonder if we'll one day be searching for a new head chef.

Text.SourceString: The idea of having another merchild crosses my mind at times, but I truly believe one, our dear Mira, is quite enough for us.
Text.LocalizedString: The idea of having another merchild crosses my mind at times, but I truly believe one, our dear Mira, is quite enough for us.

Text.SourceString: I must admit, when I learned it was this Krakatoa, the King, who was interested in courting me, I felt a sense of relief.//<portrait=normal>There was another Krakatoa, his cousin, who was part crab, and I'm glad it wasn't him!
Text.LocalizedString: I must admit, when I learned it was this Krakatoa, the King, who was interested in courting me, I felt a sense of relief.//<portrait=normal>There was another Krakatoa, his cousin, who was part crab, and I'm glad it wasn't him!

Text.SourceString: The choice of naming Miranjani wasn't really ours to make; Queen Merbabu selected it.//But I must say, I've grown to adore the name for its beauty.
Text.LocalizedString: The choice of naming Miranjani wasn't really ours to make; Queen Merbabu selected it.//But I must say, I've grown to adore the name for its beauty.

Text.SourceString: Rainfall up there brings a fresh current down here. It's soothing.
Text.LocalizedString: Rainfall up there brings a fresh current down here. It's soothing.

Text.SourceString: It must be snowing above. The water feels slightly different.
Text.LocalizedString: It must be snowing above. The water feels slightly different.

Text.SourceString: I could tell Miranjani was bored during our etiquette lesson; I hope she realizes the importance of these royal traditions.
Text.LocalizedString: I could tell Miranjani was bored during our etiquette lesson; I hope she realizes the importance of these royal traditions.

Text.SourceString: It's challenging to teach Miranjani the finer points of etiquette when her heart isn't in it; patience truly is a virtue.
Text.LocalizedString: It's challenging to teach Miranjani the finer points of etiquette when her heart isn't in it; patience truly is a virtue.

Text.SourceString: Teaching Miranjani etiquette is a royal duty, though her lack of interest was quite apparent.
Text.LocalizedString: Teaching Miranjani etiquette is a royal duty, though her lack of interest was quite apparent.

Text.SourceString: I demonstrated the weight of our responsibilities, yet Miranjani's disinterest was clear. It worries me about her future as a queen.
Text.LocalizedString: I demonstrated the weight of our responsibilities, yet Miranjani's disinterest was clear. It worries me about her future as a queen.

Text.SourceString: Reflecting on our conversation, it's clear that Miranjani's path may be different than we imagined. Her happiness is my sole target.
Text.LocalizedString: Reflecting on our conversation, it's clear that Miranjani's path may be different than we imagined. Her happiness is my sole target.

Text.SourceString: It's clear that while I once dreamt of different paths, my role as queen has always been my true calling.
Text.LocalizedString: It's clear that while I once dreamt of different paths, my role as queen has always been my true calling.

Text.SourceString: The King's words reassured me; no matter the dreams I had, my journey has led me to where I am meant to be – by his side, leading our kingdom.
Text.LocalizedString: The King's words reassured me; no matter the dreams I had, my journey has led me to where I am meant to be – by his side, leading our kingdom.

Text.SourceString: Having never worked a conventional job, I sometimes find myself questioning if I would ever be qualified for one outside of my royal duties.
Text.LocalizedString: Having never worked a conventional job, I sometimes find myself questioning if I would ever be qualified for one outside of my royal duties.

Text.SourceString: Cooking has never been my forte; I must admit, I don't think I can prepare even the simplest of meals.//<portrait=happy>Mira, however, has learned quite well, unlike me, who was always preoccupied with the preparations my mother deemed essential for a queen.
